      <h2>Initial Public Offering (IPO)</h2>

    <p>
      An Initial Public Offering (IPO) is when a private company offers its shares
      to the public for the first time and gets listed on a stock exchange.
    </p>
    <h4>Types of IPOs</h4>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Mainboard IPO:</strong>
        Large, well-established companies listed on NSE or BSE.
        These IPOs usually have higher issue sizes and stricter regulations.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>SME IPO:</strong>
        Smaller companies listed on NSE SME or BSE SME platforms.
        They offer higher growth potential but come with higher risk and lower liquidity.
      </li>
    </ul>
