      <h2>Grey Market Premium (GMP)</h2>

  <p>
    Grey Market Premium (GMP) is the unofficial price at which IPO shares
    are traded before they get listed on the stock exchange.
    It reflects market sentiment and demand for an IPO.
  </p>

  <p>
    GMP is quoted as an extra amount over the IPO issue price.
    For example, if an IPO has an issue price of ₹100 and GMP is ₹40,
    the expected listing price is around ₹140.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Positive GMP:</strong> Indicates strong demand and positive sentiment</li>
    <li><strong>Zero or Negative GMP:</strong> Signals weak interest or cautious outlook</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    GMP is driven by demand-supply dynamics, overall market conditions,
    and investor expectations around listing gains.
  </p>

  <p class="text-muted">
    GMP is not official or guaranteed — it should be used as an indicator,
    not a decision-making tool.
  </p>
